(Correction
    "Stop inventing NOTA terminology. NOTA has structs and enum variants; structs have positional fields. There is no 'head' concept — the type name appears as the first token of a record when the type is named (e.g. enum variant tag); when the type is already determined by schema position (e.g. an element of a Vec<Statement>), the name is omitted and the fields come directly. The terms 'head' and 'monomorphic position' I introduced are made-up; use NOTA's actual terms — struct, variant, positional fields, schema position."
